HEADWORD: Tufthunter
<hw>Tuft"hunt`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hanger-on to
noblemen, or persons of quality, especially in English universities; a
toady. See 1st <er>Tuft</er>, 3.</def> <mark>[Cant, Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

